AIC score

pred = colnames(AGBplots[2:9])

AICmod1pred=c()
rsemod1pred=c()
r2mod1pred=c()
RMSEmod1pred=c()
RMSErelmod1pred=c()

for(i in 1:length(pred)){
  m=lm(log(AGBplots$AGB_Ogawa_ha)~log(AGBplots[,pred[i]]))  
  AICmod1pred=c(AICmod1pred,AIC(m)) 
  
  rse = summary(m)$sigma
  rsemod1pred=c(rsemod1pred,rse) 
  
  r2 = summary(m)$r.squared
  r2mod1pred=c(r2mod1pred,r2) 
  
  AGBpredicted=exp(0.5*rse^2+predict(m))
  RMSE= sqrt(sum((AGBpredicted-AGBplots$AGB_Ogawa_ha)^2)/length(AGBpredicted))
  RMSErel=100*RMSE/mean(AGBplots$AGB_Ogawa_ha)
  
  RMSEmod1pred=c(RMSEmod1pred,RMSE) 
  RMSErelmod1pred=c(RMSErelmod1pred,RMSErel) 
}
names(AICmod1pred)=pred

#Create table
LCM_predict = data.frame(AIC = AICmod1pred , rse = rsemod1pred, r2 = r2mod1pred,
                    RMSE = RMSEmod1pred, RMSErel = RMSErelmod1pred) 

print(LCM_predict)

The best of LiDAR canopy metric for estimated AGB is Hmean

Build a LiDAR and field AGB dataset

Check relationship between LiDAR and field AGB estimates (“Hmean” is the best metric for estimated AGB)

  plot(AGB_Ogawa_ha~Hmean, data=AGBplots,log="xy", xlab="Mean TCH (m)", 
       ylab="Field AGB (Mg/ha)", pch=20)

Build a LiDAR-AGB model (linear regression)

  mod=lm(log(AGB_Ogawa_ha)~log(Hmean), data=AGBplots)
  summary(mod)

The model has a R-squared (R2) of only 0.62.

  rse = summary(mod)$sigma
  AGBpredicted = exp(0.5*rse^2+predict(mod))
  
  plot(AGBplots$AGB_Ogawa_ha,AGBpredicted,pch=20,xlab="observed AGB", ylab="predicted AGB",
       cex.lab=1.3, xlim=range(c(AGBplots$AGB_Ogawa_ha,AGBpredicted)),
       ylim=range(c(AGBplots$AGB_Ogawa_ha,AGBpredicted)),asp=1)
  abline(a=0,b=1)

Let now estimate the prediction error of the model using the Root Mean Square Error (or Deviation):

  RMSE= sqrt(sum((AGBpredicted-AGBplots$AGB_Ogawa_ha)^2)/length(AGBpredicted))
  RMSErel=100*RMSE/mean(AGBplots$AGB_Ogawa_ha)

The model has a prediction error of 20.1 %.

Apply the model to the whole CHM

Rast_Hmean = mean of CHM all footprint area at scale 50x50 m

  FunPredAGB=function(x) exp(mod$coefficients[1]+0.5*rse^2+mod$coefficients[2]*log(x))
  Rast_Hmean = aggregate(CHMlidar,50, mean, na.rm=T)
  AGBmap = lapp(Rast_Hmean, fun = FunPredAGB)
  plot(AGBmap,plg=list(title='Predicted AGB\n(Mg/ha)', title.cex=0.9))
